CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 31, 1959, pg. B2 reads: "For Office Equipment - Officers of Century Club present check for $100 for purchase of new office equipment to Miss Alvina Holt, NAACP office secretary. Left to right: Pronty L. Ford, social chairman; Richard K. Dickson, president; H. Johnson, treasurer, and Derrick Bell, Pittsburgh NAACP executive secretary."
TitMainTitle: Century Club officers, from left: Pronty L. Ford, Richard K. Dickson, H. Johnson, recipient of donation for NAACP office Alvina Holt, and Derrick Bell, in Pittsburgh NAACP office
